25|$|The first {{income tax}} {{suggested}} in the United States was during the War of 1812. The idea for the tax {{was based on the}} British Tax Act of 1798. The British tax law applied progressive rates to income. The British tax rates ranged from 0.833% on income starting at £60 to 10% on income above £200. The <b>tax</b> <b>proposal</b> was developed in 1814. Because the treaty of Ghent was signed in 1815, ending hostilities and the need for additional revenue, the tax was never imposed in the United States.|$|E
